For future readers who stumbled across the same question, there was this new fancy method added starting from Java-16 - [mapMulti][1] - it does exactly what is asked in the question and it doesn&#39;t create a new stream comparing to `flatMap`:
```
List&lt;Item&gt; itemList =
    toys.stream()
        .mapMulti(
            (Toy toy, Consumer&lt;Item&gt; consumer) -&gt; {
              consumer.accept(Item.from(toy));
              consumer.accept(Item.fromOther(toy));
            })
        .toList();
```
